    {
      "id": "_CMV0QrLMnEThFYEM-4I1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1431.590117422408,
      "y": 4352.193512577175,
      "width": 559.41259765625,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "-4ofrVWwAjmOy-duyMb8U"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bHR",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1617431773,
      "version": 1803,
      "versionNonce": 1998341459,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1737375589121,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- We have seen various ways to read sensor data, what about “writing”\nto a device? For example, we would like to send a command to our\ndevice. \n    \n- A simple HTML form that sends a POST command to the URL a led. \n    Code: 04.actuator-form.html\n\n- The method works well, unfortunately the browsers do not submit a\nJSON payload body, but use a format called \"application/x-www-form-\nurlencoded\", because of some legacy reasons\n\n- We can write function is defined which takes the data from the form,\npacks it into a JSON object, POSTs it to the Pi and displays the\nresult if successful \n    Code: 05.actuator-ajax-json.html",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- We have seen various ways to read sensor data, what about “writing” to a device? For example, we would like to send a command to our device. \n    \n- A simple HTML form that sends a POST command to the URL a led. \n    Code: 04.actuator-form.html\n\n- The method works well, unfortunately the browsers do not submit a JSON payload body, but use a format called \"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\", because of some legacy reasons\n\n- We can write function is defined which takes the data from the form, packs it into a JSON object, POSTs it to the Pi and displays the result if successful \n    Code: 05.actuator-ajax-json.html",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
