    },
    {
      "id": "301DZ6-QNvQqk2qBeUgoO",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1423.2391129581222,
      "y": 4796.153473514676,
      "width": 559.41259765625,
      "height": 340,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "qqrLQaic5ZgnfFcrGvM6z"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bHT",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 163000819,
      "version": 2000,
      "versionNonce": 1712893555,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1737375744886,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- We assumed to know what the fields of the JSON objects (e.g.\nsensor or actuator) mean and how to use them \n\n- What if the only thing we know about a device is its URL and\nnothing else?\n\n- First, we need to find the devices at a network level\n    device discovery proble\n    how can applications discover the root URL all the devices?\n\n- Second,  our application should “understand” what sensors/actuators\nthe device offers, what formats it use, and what is the meaning of\nproperties, fields, and so on \n    semantic gap\n\n- A (partial) solution: exploit the other feature of the web, links\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- We assumed to know what the fields of the JSON objects (e.g. sensor or actuator) mean and how to use them \n\n- What if the only thing we know about a device is its URL and nothing else?\n\n- First, we need to find the devices at a network level\n    device discovery proble\n    how can applications discover the root URL all the devices?\n\n- Second,  our application should “understand” what sensors/actuators the device offers, what formats it use, and what is the meaning of properties, fields, and so on \n    semantic gap\n\n- A (partial) solution: exploit the other feature of the web, links\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
