    {
      "id": "UscrkEJial1Wluwq0GleL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 776.3755255355818,
      "y": 3446.645309224134,
      "width": 559.41259765625,
      "height": 420,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "-9bRfsg2PyhOIg-usF30i"
      ],
      "frameId": "Uq24cnLJEtzbvBKHPCU4-",
      "index": "bHa",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 900199901,
      "version": 1252,
      "versionNonce": 633229555,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1736434369050,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- We can interact with the WoT from the browser, just like we browse\nthe various pages of a Web site:\n    http://devices.webofthings.io/ \n    http://devices.webofthings.io/camera/sensors/picture/ \n\n- Humans can explore the various content offered by a device and\ncontrol it from a Web page (and URLs)\n    sensors, actuators \n     \n- Notice the URL path structure\n    the URL is the root page of the gateway\n    information about the gateway itself\n    the list of devices attached to it\n\n- The page is automatically generated based on what physical devices\nare attached to it\n    it looks just like any other Web page\n    it is actually real data served in real time from real devices \n\nTry it: http://devices.webofthings.io/pi/actuators/display/ \n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- We can interact with the WoT from the browser, just like we browse the various pages of a Web site:\n    http://devices.webofthings.io/ \n    http://devices.webofthings.io/camera/sensors/picture/ \n\n- Humans can explore the various content offered by a device and control it from a Web page (and URLs)\n    sensors, actuators \n     \n- Notice the URL path structure\n    the URL is the root page of the gateway\n    information about the gateway itself\n    the list of devices attached to it\n\n- The page is automatically generated based on what physical devices are attached to it\n    it looks just like any other Web page\n    it is actually real data served in real time from real devices \n\nTry it: http://devices.webofthings.io/pi/actuators/display/ \n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
